text: Shillelagh () is a barony in County Wicklow, Republic of Ireland. ==Etymology== Shillelagh barony derives its name from the Síol Elaigh, a local people who claimed descent from Élothach mac Fáelchon, and from the village of Shillelagh. ==Location== Shillelagh barony is located in southwest County Wicklow. ==History== Derived from Síol Elaigh, meaning descendants of Ealach. O'Dunlaing (O'Dowling) was noted as a chief of Síl n-Elathaig, a branch of the Síl Mella. The Ua Tuathail (O'Tooles) were driven here in the late 12th century, following the Cambro-Norman invasion. ==List of settlements== Below is a list of settlements in Shillelagh barony: *Carnew *Coolboy *Shillelagh ==References== Category:Baronies of County Wicklow
